Alphabet Triangle Pattern


The program must accept an alphabet CH as the input.
The program must print the desired pattern as shown in the Example 
Input/Output section.
Input Format:The first line contains the alphabet CH.
Output Format:The lines containing the desired pattern as shown in the Example 
Input/Output section.Example Input/Output 1:Input:F
Output:

A
B B
C C C
D D D D
E E E E E
F F F F F F
Example Input/Output 2:
Input:gOutput:
A
B B
C C C
D D D D
E E E E E
F F F F F F
G G G G G G G
Max Execution Time Limit: 1000 millisecs

CODE:
#include<stdio.h>#include <stdlib.h>
int main()
{ 
char ch,s; 
scanf("%c",&ch); 
s=(ch>='A' && ch<='Z')?ch:(ch-32); 
int i,j;
for(i='A';i<=s;i++)
{ 
for(j='A';j<=i;j++) 
{
printf("%c",i); 
} 
printf("\n");
}
}

or
ASCII VALUE OF A IS 65
               Z IS 9


#include<stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
int main()
{ 
char ch,s; 
scanf("%c",&ch); 
s=(ch>='A' && ch<='Z')?ch:(ch-32); 
int i,j;
for(i=1;i<=((s-65)+1);i++)
{ 
    
for(j=1;j<=i;j++) 
{
printf("%c",'A'+i-1); 
} 
printf("\n");
}
}
